title: For Sale/Trade:  Yugo M48A Mauser w/ Balkan Trench Art - Project Gun
postcontent: For sale or trade is my Yugoslavian M48A mauser pattern rifle. The good: This rifle shows strong indications of having served in the Balkan Wars of the 1990's. This is evidenced by a Serbian nationalist image carved in the stock. The image is a simplified Serbian Cross with what appear to be four "C's (actually cyrillic "S's). This is an acronym for "Samo Sloga Srbina Spasava" (Only Unity Saves the Serbs). That slogan and the corresponding symbol were used heavily during the Croatian and Bosnian wars, and are very commonly found carved into the stocks of AK and SKS pattern rifles from that time. Seeing that image on an M48 however, is much less common, and seems to imply that this is a rather special example. Additionally, the wear on the rifle is consistent with a rifle which has seen battle. The buttplate is pitted and rough, the finish is heavily but evenly worn, and the trigger group is exceptionally broken in.The bad: The bolt body on this rifle needs to be repaired or replaced. A slight imperfection in the geometry of the boltface lip prevents this rifle from properly seating cartridges. The rifle will not reliably cycle rounds. In order to restore this rifle to full function either: A) The current bolt face will need to be carefully reprofiled -OR- a new intermediate length bolt body will need to be fit to the rifle. Numrich currently sells stripped Belgian 1924 bolts, which can be fit to M48s. I may or may not have such a stripped bolt available with this rifle, inquire if interested.The mundane: Overall condition of the firearm would be "Surplus Good". I have detail stripped this rifle. Magazine body and trigger guard have cosmetic pitting. Barrel bands and rifle have minimal corrosion, but moderate to heavy finish wear. Stock has been knocked around a bit, but has no signficant dents, and absolutely no cracks. Stock and Reciever match. Bolt, Rear Sight, and mag plate do not match. Bore is very good.This rifle is specificallly designated as a Curio and Relic by the ATF (27 CFR 478.11), and therefor DOES NOT require a background check for private transfer in the State of Colroado (CRS 18-12-112 6(a)). As such, the buyer of this rifle will not be subject to any transfer fees. I will require a photo ID with proof of age (CO law requires 18+). Prospective buyers able to present a valid CHP or other proof of recent background check will be given preference.

title: For Sale:  Romanian PSL Dragunov sniper rifle
postcontent: A Parts kit built Romanian PSL Dragunov sniper rifle built on a Nodak Spud receiver. The rifles wood has been refinished and looks amazing.The PSL has been in service in Romania since the 1970s and is widely sold on the world market. They are frequently encountered in Iraq where they appear to be quite popular. The simplicity of the rifle makes it ideal for soldiers to use and maintain. The action, being a variant of the AKM's, is extremely reliable despite lack of maintenance, and is particularly forgiving of sand and other debris. The scope's reticle pattern is easy to use and makes range estimation quick and reasonably accurate without any mathematical calculations necessary. With some simple instruction an average individual can be issued a PSL and successfully engage targets at ranges that far exceed the accurate capabilities of non-scoped assault rifles like the AKM, AK-47, etc. Accuracy varies greatly, however, between individual rifles to a greater extent to other rifles in its class, probably due to insufficient quality control during the manufacturing process. In the hands of a capable shooter and with quality ammunition such as 7N1 and 7N14 a PSL is capable of 1 Minute of angle (approximately 1" at 100 yards) or less while the rifles on the other end of the spectrum are only capable of about 3 MOA. Complete with original military scope. These rifles are also known as a Romak-3 PSL and SSG-97 and are extremely accurate/reliable. This gun is the Romanian version (PSL). This is a great Rifle for many reasons. The PSL rifle's primary purpose is to be used by a platoon level designated marksman to engage targets at ranges beyond the capabilities of the standard issue AKM carbines. It is built around a stamped steel receiver similar to that of the RPK light machine gun, having a wider forward section enabling a strengthened, more substantial front trunnion. The PSL's operation is the same long stroke piston action of the Kalashnikov family of weapons. Its appearance is similar to the Dragunov sniper rifle yet not one single part interchanges between the rifles. It's semi-automatic and it uses very powerful 7.62x54R caliber ammo. which is a Very Large round. Bigger then .308 The PSL is chambered for the same venerable 7.62x54mmR (rimmed) cartridge as the Dragunov, and feeds from a ten-round detachable box magazine. The magazine used on the PSL differs from that of Dragunov models in that it is stamped with an X shaped pattern on the side, rather than the waffle style stamp found on the Russian and Chinese magazines. The magazines, though they are similar in shape and size, are not interchangeable between the Dragunov and PSL without modification. The size of this round (7.62x54R) and the long barrel of the rifle allow shooting out to 1000yards plus. These features make the perfect long range Riffle for any situation. Comes with Two 10 round mags and a cleaning kit and sling. This rifle comes complete with scope that has a built in range finder reticle which was originally lit with radioactive Tritium and is still going strong.

With some simple instruction an average individual can be issued a PSL and successfully engage targets at ranges that far exceed the accurate capabilities of non-scoped assault rifles like the AKM, AK-47, etc. Accuracy varies greatly, however, between individual rifles to a greater extent to other rifles in its class, probably due to insufficient quality control during the manufacturing process. In the hands of a capable shooter and with quality ammunition such as 7N1 and 7N14 a PSL is capable of 1 Minute of angle (approximately 1" at 100 yards) or less while the rifles on the other end of the spectrum are only capable of about 3 MOA. Complete with original military scope. These rifles are also known as a Romak-3 PSL and SSG-97 and are extremely accurate/reliable. This gun is the Romanian version (PSL). This is a great Rifle for many reasons. The PSL rifle's primary purpose is to be used by a platoon level designated marksman to engage targets at ranges beyond the capabilities of the standard issue AKM carbines. It is built around a stamped steel receiver similar to that of the RPK light machine gun, having a wider forward section enabling a strengthened, more substantial front trunnion. The PSL's operation is the same long stroke piston action of the Kalashnikov family of weapons. Its appearance is similar to the Dragunov sniper rifle yet not one single part interchanges between the rifles. It's semi-automatic and it uses very powerful 7.62x54R caliber ammo. which is a Very Large round. Bigger then .308 The PSL is chambered for the same venerable 7.62x54mmR (rimmed) cartridge as the Dragunov, and feeds from a ten-round detachable box magazine. The magazine used on the PSL differs from that of Dragunov models in that it is stamped with an X shaped pattern on the side, rather than the waffle style stamp found on the Russian and Chinese magazines. The magazines, though they are similar in shape and size, are not interchangeable between the Dragunov and PSL without modification. The size of this round (7.62x54R) and the long barrel of the rifle allow shooting out to 1000yards plus. These features make the perfect long range Riffle for any situation. Comes with Two 10 round mags and a cleaning kit and sling. This rifle comes complete with scope that has a built in range finder reticle which was originally lit with radioactive Tritium and is still going strong.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Golani Galil 5.56
postcontent: This is the newer Golani Galil milled receiver AK that shoots the .223 and military 5.56 round. It comes with 10 large capacity mags (possibly more if I can find them). The Galil is a milled steel receiver that comes with a heavy folding metal stock, removeable muzzle break, threaded barrel and has a matte black finish. These guns are also famous for having a far better quality than your typical AK series rifle on the market. They have tighter tolerances, better fitment, and shoot a much tighter group than your run of the mill AK. The Galil is considered the AK of the Israeli world and is known worldwide. It not only comes with the typical AK style bar safety on the right side of the receiver, but also has a thumb safety on the left hand side of the receiver as well. It is a milled steel receiver, not stamped like your typical AK47 or forged like your average AR15. Because of this, it is considered one of the most durable battle proven rifles on the market.If you have never fired a Galil before, you will find it to be one of the smoothest firing/recoiling piston systems around. This isnt like shooting an AK47, where there is that harsh upper left hand recoil, but more of a manageable smooth recoil that allows you to execute fast double taps with very little muzzle rise. Cash is king as with all things, but I am VERY open to trades of any sort for the most part. I am primarily looking for firearms, ammo, optics trades. I will be upfront and say I am NOT looking for lawnmowers, or sound systems, or extremely cheap firearms, so please do not waste yours or my time. I will answer all emails, if anything, to say no thank you for your offer, but I do appreciate you taking the time to make me an offer. IF YOU ARE EMAILING ME AN TRADE OFFER, PLEASE DO ME THE COURTESY AND INCLUDE A DETAILED DESCRIPTION AS WELL AS PHOTOS OF WHAT YOU ARE WANTING TO POSSIBLY TRADE. IF YOU WERE THE ONE POSTING AN AD, IM SURE YOU WOULD WANT THESE AS WELL. THIS ALSO HELPS ME DECIDE IF A TRADE IS SOMETHING I WOULD BE INTERESTED IN.
